eNCA reporter Heidi Giokos is covering this for us. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The country’s current COVID-19 regulations and policy objectives are unclear and not consistent, that’s according to UKZN’s Research and Innovation Vice-Chancellor Professor Mosa Moshabela. Moshabela says the government needs to clarify whether the regulations are there to prevent the spread of the virus or are for protecting people from severe illness, hospitalisation, and death. READ | Nearly 30m under lockdown in China as coronavirus surges There have been growing calls for the government to lift COVID-19 regulations like the wearing of masks. Meanwhile, President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to address the nation on the COVID-19 response at 8pm on Tuesday.